com.vmware.appliance.vcenter.settings.v1.config.components.inventory.cluster.ha

Class FailuresAndResponses

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.vmware.appliance.vcenter.settings.v1.config.components.inventory.cluster.ha.FailuresAndResponses
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    StaticStructure, Structure, java.io.Serializable

    public final class FailuresAndResponses
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, StaticStructure
    The FailuresAndResponses class contains properties describing the Failures and responses specific configurations of a cluster. It contains cluster-wide configurations for vsphere HA.
    See Also:

      • getRestartPriorityConditionTimeout

        public java.lang.Long getRestartPriorityConditionTimeout()
        This setting is used to specify a maximum time the lower priority VMs should wait for the higher priority VMs to be ready. If the higher priority Vms are not ready by this time, then the lower priority VMs are restarted irrespective of the VM ready state. This timeout can be used to prevent the failover of lower priority VMs to be stuck infinitely. Timeout specified in seconds. To use cluster setting for a VM override, set to -1 in per-VM. setting.

        If null or empty, the value is skipped.
        Returns:
        The current value of the property.

If the higher priority Vms are not ready by this time, then the lower priority VMs are restarted irrespective of the VM ready state. This timeout can be used to prevent the failover of lower priority VMs to be stuck infinitely. Timeout specified in seconds. To use cluster setting for a VM override, set to -1 in per-VM. setting.

      • getResponseRecovery

        public FailuresAndResponses.VmReactionOnAPDCleared getResponseRecovery()
        Action taken by VM Component Protection service for a powered on VM when APD condition clears after APD timeout.

        This property is meaningful only when vSphere HA is turned on. Valid values are specified by FailuresAndResponses.VmReactionOnAPDCleared. The default value is VmReactionOnAPDCleared#none for cluster setting and VmReactionOnAPDCleared#useClusterDefault for per-VM setting.

        The current value of the property.
